  "description": "Semiconductor-grade photomask substrate production: fused silica blanks with <250 nm flatness over 152 mm, ULE (ultra-low expansion) titanium silicate glass with near-zero CTE (0±30 ppb/°C) for EUV lithography, precision polishing to <0.5 nm RMS roughness, chromium film sputtering, and defect inspection to sub-micron levels. The dimensional stability and optical quality of photomask glass directly determines achievable feature size in IC fabrication.",
